docsBpi2MIB.description: This is the MIB module for the DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface (BPI+) at cable modems (CMs) and cable modem termination systems (CMTSs). Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2005). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4131; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

DocsX509ASN1DEREncodedCertificate.name: DocsX509ASN1DEREncodedCertificate
DocsX509ASN1DEREncodedCertificate.description: An X509 digital certificate encoded as an ASN.1 DER object.

DocsSAId.name: DocsSAId
DocsSAId.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface specification, Section 2.1.3, BPI+ Security Associations

DocsSAIdOrZero.name: DocsSAIdOrZero
DocsSAIdOrZero.description: Security Association identifier (SAID). The value zero indicates that the SAID is yet to be determined.
DocsSAIdOrZero.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface specification, Section 2.1.3, BPI+ Security Associations

DocsBpkmSAType.name: DocsBpkmSAType
DocsBpkmSAType.description: The type of security association (SA). The values of the named-numbers are associated with the BPKM SA-Type attributes: 'primary' corresponds to code '1', 'static' to code '2', and 'dynamic' to code '3'. The 'none' value must only be used if the SA type has yet to be determined.
DocsBpkmSAType.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface specification, Section 4.2.2.24

DocsBpkmDataEncryptAlg.name: DocsBpkmDataEncryptAlg
DocsBpkmDataEncryptAlg.description: The list of data encryption algorithms defined for the DOCSIS interface in the BPKM cryptographic-suite parameter. The value 'none' indicates that the SAID being referenced has no data encryption.
DocsBpkmDataEncryptAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.

DocsBpkmDataAuthentAlg.name: DocsBpkmDataAuthentAlg
DocsBpkmDataAuthentAlg.description: The list of data integrity algorithms defined for the DOCSIS interface in the BPKM cryptographic-suite parameter. The value 'none' indicates that no data integrity is used for the SAID being referenced.
DocsBpkmDataAuthentAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.

docsBpi2CmBaseTable.name: docsBpi2CmBaseTable
docsBpi2CmBaseTable.description: This table describes the basic and authorization- related Baseline Privacy Plus attributes of each CM MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmBaseEntry.name: docsBpi2CmBaseEntry
docsBpi2CmBaseEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing attributes of one CM MAC interface. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsBpi2CmPrivacyEnable.name: docsBpi2CmPrivacyEnable
docsBpi2CmPrivacyEnable.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.
docsBpi2CmPrivacyEnable.description: This object identifies whether this CM is provisioned to run Baseline Privacy Plus.

docsBpi2CmPublicKey.name: docsBpi2CmPublicKey
docsBpi2CmPublicKey.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.4.
docsBpi2CmPublicKey.description: The value of this object is a DER-encoded RSAPublicKey ASN.1 type string, as defined in the RSA Encryption Standard (PKCS #1), corresponding to the public key of the CM.

docsBpi2CmAuthState.name: docsBpi2CmAuthState
docsBpi2CmAuthState.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.1.2.1.
docsBpi2CmAuthState.description: The value of this object is the state of the CM authorization FSM. The start state indicates that FSM is in its initial state.

docsBpi2CmAuthKeySequenceNumber.name: docsBpi2CmAuthKeySequenceNumber
docsBpi2CmAuthKeySequenceNumber.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.10.
docsBpi2CmAuthKeySequenceNumber.description: The value of this object is the most recent authorization key sequence number for this FSM.

docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresOld.name: docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresOld
docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresOld.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresOld.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the immediate predecessor of the most recent authorization key for this FSM. If this FSM has only one authorization key, then the value is the time of activation of this FSM.

docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresNew.name: docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresNew
docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresNew.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmAuthExpiresNew.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the most recent authorization key for this FSM.

docsBpi2CmAuthReset.name: docsBpi2CmAuthReset
docsBpi2CmAuthReset.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.1.2.3.4.
docsBpi2CmAuthReset.description: Setting this object to 'true' generates a Reauthorize event in the authorization FSM. Reading this object always returns FALSE. This object is for testing purposes only, and therefore it is not required to be associated with a last reset object.

docsBpi2CmAuthGraceTime.name: docsBpi2CmAuthGraceTime
docsBpi2CmAuthGraceTime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.3.
docsBpi2CmAuthGraceTime.description: The value of this object is the grace time for an authorization key in seconds. A CM is expected to start trying to get a new authorization key beginning AuthGraceTime seconds before the most recent authorization key actually expires.

docsBpi2CmTEKGraceTime.name: docsBpi2CmTEKGraceTime
docsBpi2CmTEKGraceTime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.6.
docsBpi2CmTEKGraceTime.description: The value of this object is the grace time for the TEK in seconds. The CM is expected to start trying to acquire a new TEK beginning TEK GraceTime seconds before the expiration of the most recent TEK.

docsBpi2CmAuthWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmAuthWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmAuthWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.1.
docsBpi2CmAuthWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the Authorize Wait Timeout in seconds.

docsBpi2CmReauthWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmReauthWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmReauthWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.2.
docsBpi2CmReauthWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the Reauthorize Wait Timeout in seconds.

docsBpi2CmOpWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmOpWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmOpWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.4.
docsBpi2CmOpWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the Operational Wait Timeout in seconds.

docsBpi2CmRekeyWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmRekeyWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmRekeyWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.5.
docsBpi2CmRekeyWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the Rekey Wait Timeout in seconds.

docsBpi2CmAuthRejectWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmAuthRejectWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.7.
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the Authorization Reject Wait Timeout in seconds.

docsBpi2CmSAMapWaitTimeout.name: docsBpi2CmSAMapWaitTimeout
docsBpi2CmSAMapWaitTimeout.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.8.
docsBpi2CmSAMapWaitTimeout.description: The value of this object is the retransmission interval, in seconds, of SA Map Requests from the MAP Wait state.

docsBpi2CmSAMapMaxRetries.name: docsBpi2CmSAMapMaxRetries
docsBpi2CmSAMapMaxRetries.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.1.1.1.9.
docsBpi2CmSAMapMaxRetries.description: The value of this object is the maximum number of Map Request retries allowed.

docsBpi2CmAuthentInfos.name: docsBpi2CmAuthentInfos
docsBpi2CmAuthentInfos.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.9.
docsBpi2CmAuthentInfos.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has transmitted an Authentication Information message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmAuthRequests.name: docsBpi2CmAuthRequests
docsBpi2CmAuthRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.1.
docsBpi2CmAuthRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has transmitted an Authorization Request message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmAuthReplies.name: docsBpi2CmAuthReplies
docsBpi2CmAuthReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.2.
docsBpi2CmAuthReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received an Authorization Reply message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmAuthRejects.name: docsBpi2CmAuthRejects
docsBpi2CmAuthRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmAuthRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received an Authorization Reject message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmAuthInvalids.name: docsBpi2CmAuthInvalids
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalids.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.7.
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalids.description: The value of this object is the count of times the CM has received an Authorization Invalid message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.3 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Authorization Reject message received by the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Authorization Reject message has been received since reboot.

docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.3 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmAuthRejectErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Authorization Reject message received by the CM. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Reject message has been received since reboot.

docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorCode
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.7 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Authorization Invalid message received by the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Authorization Invalid message has been received since reboot.

docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorString
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.7 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmAuthInvalidErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Authorization Invalid message received by the CM. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Invalid message has been received since reboot.

docsBpi2CmTEKTable.name: docsBpi2CmTEKTable
docsBpi2CmTEKTable.description: This table describes the attributes of each CM Traffic Encryption Key (TEK) association. The CM maintains (no more than) one TEK association per SAID per CM MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmTEKEntry.name: docsBpi2CmTEKEntry
docsBpi2CmTEKEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing the TEK association attributes of one SAID. The CM MUST create one entry per SAID, regardless of whether the SAID was obtained from a Registration Response message, from an Authorization Reply message, or from any dynamic SAID establishment mechanisms.

docsBpi2CmTEKSAId.name: docsBpi2CmTEKSAId
docsBpi2CmTEKSAId.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.12.
docsBpi2CmTEKSAId.description: The value of this object is the DOCSIS Security Association ID (SAID).

docsBpi2CmTEKSAType.name: docsBpi2CmTEKSAType
docsBpi2CmTEKSAType.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmTEKSAType.description: The value of this object is the type of security association.

docsBpi2CmTEKDataEncryptAlg.name: docsBpi2CmTEKDataEncryptAlg
docsBpi2CmTEKDataEncryptAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmTEKDataEncryptAlg.description: The value of this object is the data encryption algorithm for this SAID.

docsBpi2CmTEKDataAuthentAlg.name: docsBpi2CmTEKDataAuthentAlg
docsBpi2CmTEKDataAuthentAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmTEKDataAuthentAlg.description: The value of this object is the data authentication algorithm for this SAID.

docsBpi2CmTEKState.name: docsBpi2CmTEKState
docsBpi2CmTEKState.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.1.3.1.
docsBpi2CmTEKState.description: The value of this object is the state of the indicated TEK FSM. The start(1) state indicates that the FSM is in its initial state.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeySequenceNumber.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeySequenceNumber
docsBpi2CmTEKKeySequenceNumber.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.2.10 and 4.2.2.13.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeySequenceNumber.description: The value of this object is the most recent TEK key sequence number for this TEK FSM.

docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresOld.name: docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresOld
docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresOld.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.5 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresOld.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the immediate predecessor of the most recent TEK for this FSM. If this FSM has only one TEK, then the value is the time of activation of this FSM.

docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresNew.name: docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresNew
docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresNew.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.5 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmTEKExpiresNew.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the most recent TEK for this FSM.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRequests.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRequests
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.4.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has transmitted a Key Request message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeyReplies.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeyReplies
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.5.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received a Key Reply message, including a message whose authentication failed. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejects.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejects
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.6.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received a Key Reject message, including a message whose authentication failed. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmTEKInvalids.name: docsBpi2CmTEKInvalids
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalids.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.8.
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalids.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received a TEK Invalid message, including a message whose authentication failed. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmTEKAuthPends.name: docsBpi2CmTEKAuthPends
docsBpi2CmTEKAuthPends.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.1.3.3.3.
docsBpi2CmTEKAuthPends.description: The value of this object is the count of times an Authorization Pending (Auth Pend) event occurred in this FSM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.1.2.6 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Key Reject message received by the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Key Reject message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.1.2.6 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmTEKKeyRejectErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Key Reject message received by the CM. This is a zero length string if no Key Reject message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorCode
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.1.2.8 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent TEK Invalid message received by the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no TEK Invalid message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorString
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.1.2.8 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmTEKInvalidErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent TEK Invalid message received by the CM. This is a zero length string if no TEK Invalid message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapTable.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapTable
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapTable.description: This table maps multicast IP addresses to SAIDs per CM MAC Interface. It is intended to map multicast IP addresses associated with SA MAP Request messages.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapEntry.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapEntry
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastMapEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing the mapping of one multicast IP address to one SAID, as well as associated state, message counters, and error information. An entry may be removed from this table upon the reception of an SA Map Reject.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddressType.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddressType
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddressType.description: The type of Internet address for docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddress.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddress.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddress
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddress.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 5.4.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddress.description: This object represents the IP multicast address to be mapped. The type of this address is determined by the value of the docsBpi2CmIpMulticastAddressType object.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAId.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAId
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAId.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.12.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAId.description: This object represents the SAID to which the IP multicast address has been mapped. If no SA Map Reply has been received for the IP address, this object should have the value 0.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapState.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapState
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapState.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 5.3.1.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapState.description: The value of this object is the state of the SA Mapping FSM for this IP.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRequests.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRequests
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.10.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has transmitted an SA Map Request message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapReplies.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapReplies
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.11.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received an SA Map Reply message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejects.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejects
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.12.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CM has received an SA MAP Reject message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorCod.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorCod.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.12 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorCod.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent SA Map Reject message sent in response to an SA Map Request for This IP. It has the value none(1) if no SA MAP Reject message has been received since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorStr.name: docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorStr.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.12 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorStr.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent SA Map Reject message sent in response to an SA Map Request for this IP. It is a zero length string if no SA Map Reject message has been received since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmDeviceCertTable.name: docsBpi2CmDeviceCertTable
docsBpi2CmDeviceCertTable.description: This table describes the Baseline Privacy Plus device certificates for each CM MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmDeviceCertEntry.name: docsBpi2CmDeviceCertEntry
docsBpi2CmDeviceCertEntry.description: Each entry contains the device certificates of one CM MAC interface. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsBpi2CmDeviceCmCert.name: docsBpi2CmDeviceCmCert
docsBpi2CmDeviceCmCert.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.1.
docsBpi2CmDeviceCmCert.description: The X509 DER-encoded cable modem certificate. Note: This object can be set only when the value is the zero-length OCTET STRING; otherwise, an error of 'inconsistentValue' is returned. Once the object contains the certificate, its access MUST be read-only and persists after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmDeviceManufCert.name: docsBpi2CmDeviceManufCert
docsBpi2CmDeviceManufCert.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.1.
docsBpi2CmDeviceManufCert.description: The X509 DER-encoded manufacturer certificate that signed the cable modem certificate.

docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteTable.name: docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteTable
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteTable.description: This table describes the Baseline Privacy Plus cryptographic suite capabilities for each CM MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteEntry.name: docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteEntry
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteEntry.description: Each entry contains a cryptographic suite pair that this CM MAC supports.

docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteIndex.name: docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteIndex
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteIndex.description: The index for a cryptographic suite row.

docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataEncryptAlg.name: docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataEncryptAlg
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataEncryptAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataEncryptAlg.description: The value of this object is the data encryption algorithm for this cryptographic suite capability.

docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataAuthentAlg.name: docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataAuthentAlg
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataAuthentAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmCryptoSuiteDataAuthentAlg.description: The value of this object is the data authentication algorithm for this cryptographic suite capability.

docsBpi2CmtsBaseTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsBaseTable
docsBpi2CmtsBaseTable.description: This table describes the basic Baseline Privacy attributes of each CMTS MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmtsBaseEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsBaseEntry
docsBpi2CmtsBaseEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing attributes of one CMTS MAC interface. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsBpi2CmtsDefaultAuthLifetime.name: docsBpi2CmtsDefaultAuthLifetime
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultAuthLifetime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.2.
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultAuthLifetime.description: The value of this object is the default lifetime, in seconds, that the CMTS assigns to a new authorization key. This object value persists after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsDefaultTEKLifetime.name: docsBpi2CmtsDefaultTEKLifetime
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultTEKLifetime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Appendix A.2.
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultTEKLifetime.description: The value of this object is the default lifetime, in seconds, that the CMTS assigns to a new Traffic Encryption Key (TEK). This object value persists after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsDefaultSelfSignedManufCertTr.name: docsBpi2CmtsDefaultSelfSignedManufCertTrust
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultSelfSignedManufCertTr.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.1
docsBpi2CmtsDefaultSelfSignedManufCertTr.description: This object determines the default trust of self-signed manufacturer certificate entries, contained in docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable, and created after this object is set. This object need not persist after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsCheckCertValidityPeriods.name: docsBpi2CmtsCheckCertValidityPeriods
docsBpi2CmtsCheckCertValidityPeriods.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.2
docsBpi2CmtsCheckCertValidityPeriods.description: Setting this object to 'true' causes all chained and root certificates in the chain to have their validity periods checked against the current time of day, when the CMTS receives an Authorization Request from the CM. A 'false' setting causes all certificates in the chain not to have their validity periods checked against the current time of day. This object need not persist after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthentInfos.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthentInfos
docsBpi2CmtsAuthentInfos.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.9.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthentInfos.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an Authentication Information message from any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthRequests.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthRequests
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.1.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an Authorization Request message from any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthReplies.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthReplies
docsBpi2CmtsAuthReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Reply message to any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejects.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejects
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Reject message to any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalids.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalids
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalids.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.7.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalids.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Invalid message to any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRequests.name: docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRequests
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.10.
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an SA Map Request message from any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsSAMapReplies.name: docsBpi2CmtsSAMapReplies
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.11.
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an SA Map Reply message to any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRejects.name: docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRejects
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.12.
docsBpi2CmtsSAMapRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an SA Map Reject message to any CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthTable
docsBpi2CmtsAuthTable.description: This table describes the attributes of each CM authorization association. The CMTS maintains one authorization association with each Baseline Privacy- enabled CM, registered on each CMTS MAC interface, regardless of whether the CM is authorized or rejected.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthEntry
docsBpi2CmtsAuthEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing attributes of one authorization association. The CMTS MUST create one entry per CM per MAC interface, based on the receipt of an Authorization Request message, and MUST not delete the entry until the CM loses registration.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmMacAddress.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmMacAddress
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmMacAddress.description: The value of this object is the physical address of the CM to which the authorization association applies.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmBpiVersion.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmBpiVersion
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmBpiVersion.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.22; ANSI/SCTE 22-2 2002(formerly DSS 02-03) Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specification DOCSIS 1.0 Baseline Privacy Interface (BPI)
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmBpiVersion.description: The value of this object is the version of Baseline Privacy for which this CM has registered. The value 'bpiplus' represents the value of BPI-Version Attribute of the Baseline Privacy Key Management BPKM attribute BPI-Version (1). The value 'bpi' is used to represent the CM registered using DOCSIS 1.0 Baseline Privacy.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmPublicKey.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmPublicKey
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmPublicKey.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.4.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmPublicKey.description: The value of this object is a DER-encoded RSAPublicKey ASN.1 type string, as defined in the RSA Encryption Standard (PKCS #1), corresponding to the public key of the CM. This is the zero-length OCTET STRING if the CMTS does not retain the public key.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmKeySequenceNumber.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmKeySequenceNumber
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmKeySequenceNumber.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.10.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmKeySequenceNumber.description: The value of this object is the most recent authorization key sequence number for this CM.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresOld.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresOld
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresOld.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresOld.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the immediate predecessor of the most recent authorization key for this FSM. If this FSM has only one authorization key, then the value is the time of activation of this FSM. Note: This object has no meaning for CMs running in BPI mode; therefore, this object is not instantiated for entries associated to those CMs.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresNew.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresNew
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresNew.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.2 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmExpiresNew.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the most recent authorization key for this FSM.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmLifetime.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmLifetime
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmLifetime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.2 and Appendix A.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmLifetime.description: The value of this object is the lifetime, in seconds, that the CMTS assigns to an authorization key for this CM.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReset.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReset
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReset.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.1.2.3.4, 4.1.2.3.5, and 4.1.3.3.5.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReset.description: Setting this object to invalidateAuth(2) causes the CMTS to invalidate the current CM authorization key(s), but not to transmit an Authorization Invalid message nor to invalidate the primary SAID's TEKs. Setting this object to sendAuthInvalid(3) causes the CMTS to invalidate the current CM authorization key(s), and to transmit an Authorization Invalid message to the CM, but not to invalidate the primary SAID's TEKs. Setting this object to invalidateTeks(4) causes the CMTS to invalidate the current CM authorization key(s), to transmit an Authorization Invalid message to the CM, and to invalidate the TEKs associated with this CM's primary SAID. For BPI mode, substitute all of the CM's unicast TEKs for the primary SAID's TEKs in the previous paragraph. Reading this object returns the most recently set value of this object or, if the object has not been set since entry creation, returns noResetRequested(1).

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInfos.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInfos
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInfos.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.9.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInfos.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an Authentication Information message from this CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRequests.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRequests
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.1.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an Authorization Request message from this CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReplies.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReplies
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Reply message to this CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRejects.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRejects
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Reject message to this CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInvalids.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInvalids
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInvalids.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.7.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCmInvalids.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an Authorization Invalid message to this CM. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.3 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Authorization Reject message transmitted to the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Authorization Reject message has been transmitted to the CM since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.3 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthRejectErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Authorization Reject message transmitted to the CM. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Reject message has been transmitted to the CM since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorCode
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.7 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Authorization Invalid message transmitted to the CM. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Authorization Invalid message has been transmitted to the CM since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorString
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.7 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthInvalidErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Authorization Invalid message transmitted to the CM. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Invalid message has been transmitted to the CM since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthPrimarySAId.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthPrimarySAId
docsBpi2CmtsAuthPrimarySAId.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthPrimarySAId.description: The value of this object is the Primary Security Association identifier. For BPI mode, the value must be any unicast SID.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCertValid.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCertValid
docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCertValid.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCertValid.description: Contains the reason why a CM's certificate is deemed valid or invalid. Return unknown(0) if the CM is running BPI mode. ValidCmChained(1) means the certificate is valid because it chains to a valid certificate. ValidCmTrusted(2) means the certificate is valid because it has been provisioned (in the docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert table) to be trusted. InvalidCmUntrusted(3) means the certificate is invalid because it has been provisioned (in the docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert table) to be untrusted. InvalidCAUntrusted(4) means the certificate is invalid because it chains to an untrusted certificate. InvalidCmOther(5) and InvalidCAOther(6) refer to errors in parsing, validity periods, etc., which are attributable to the CM certificate or its chain, respectively; additional information may be found in docsBpi2AuthRejectErrorString for these types of errors.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCert.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCert
docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCert.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthBpkmCmCert.description: The X509 CM Certificate sent as part of a BPKM Authorization Request. Note: The zero-length OCTET STRING must be returned if the Entire certificate is not retained in the CMTS.

docsBpi2CmtsAuthCACertIndexPtr.name: docsBpi2CmtsAuthCACertIndexPtr
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCACertIndexPtr.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.
docsBpi2CmtsAuthCACertIndexPtr.description: A row index into docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable. Returns the index in docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable to which CA certificate this CM is chained to. A value of 0 means it could not be found or not applicable.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKTable
docsBpi2CmtsTEKTable.description: This table describes the attributes of each Traffic Encryption Key (TEK) association. The CMTS Maintains one TEK association per SAID on each CMTS MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKEntry
docsBpi2CmtsTEKEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing attributes of one TEK association on a particular CMTS MAC interface. The CMTS MUST create one entry per SAID per MAC interface, based on the receipt of a Key Request message, and MUST not delete the entry before the CM authorization for the SAID permanently expires.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAId.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAId
docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAId.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.12.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAId.description: The value of this object is the DOCSIS Security Association ID (SAID).

docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAType.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAType
docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAType.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKSAType.description: The value of this object is the type of security association. 'dynamic' does not apply to CMs running in BPI mode. Unicast BPI TEKs must utilize the 'primary' encoding, and multicast BPI TEKs must utilize the 'static' encoding.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataEncryptAlg.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataEncryptAlg
docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataEncryptAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataEncryptAlg.description: The value of this object is the data encryption algorithm for this SAID.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataAuthentAlg.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataAuthentAlg
docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataAuthentAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKDataAuthentAlg.description: The value of this object is the data authentication algorithm for this SAID.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKLifetime.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKLifetime
docsBpi2CmtsTEKLifetime.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.5 and Appendix A.2.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKLifetime.description: The value of this object is the lifetime, in seconds, that the CMTS assigns to keys for this TEK association.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKKeySequenceNumber.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKKeySequenceNumber
docsBpi2CmtsTEKKeySequenceNumber.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.2.10 and 4.2.2.13.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKKeySequenceNumber.description: The value of this object is the most recent TEK key sequence number for this SAID.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresOld.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresOld
docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresOld.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.5 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresOld.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the immediate predecessor of the most recent TEK for this FSM. If this FSM has only one TEK, then the value is the time of activation of this FSM.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresNew.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresNew
docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresNew.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.5 and 4.2.2.9.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKExpiresNew.description: The value of this object is the actual clock time for expiration of the most recent TEK for this FSM.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKReset.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKReset
docsBpi2CmtsTEKReset.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.1.3.3.5.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKReset.description: Setting this object to 'true' causes the CMTS to invalidate all currently active TEKs and to generate new TEKs for the associated SAID; the CMTS MAY also generate unsolicited TEK Invalid messages, to optimize the TEK synchronization between the CMTS and the CM(s). Reading this object always returns FALSE.

docsBpi2CmtsKeyRequests.name: docsBpi2CmtsKeyRequests
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.4.
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received a Key Request message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsKeyReplies.name: docsBpi2CmtsKeyReplies
docsBpi2CmtsKeyReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.5.
docsBpi2CmtsKeyReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted a Key Reply message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejects.name: docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejects
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.6.
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted a Key Reject message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalids.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalids
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalids.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.8.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalids.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted a TEK Invalid message. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.6 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent Key Reject message sent in response to a Key Request for this SAID. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no Key Reject message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.6 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmtsKeyRejectErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent Key Reject message sent in response to a Key Request for this SAID. This is a zero length string if no Key Reject message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorCode.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorCode
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.8 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorCode.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent TEK Invalid message sent in association with this SAID. This has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code value was 0 and none(1) if no TEK Invalid message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorString.name: docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorString
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.8 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmtsTEKInvalidErrorString.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent TEK Invalid message sent in association with this SAID. This is a zero length string if no TEK Invalid message has been received since registration.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapTable
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapTable.description: This table maps multicast IP addresses to SAIDs. If a multicast IP address is mapped by multiple rows in the table, the row with the lowest docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastIndex must be utilized for the mapping.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapEntry
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing the mapping of a set of multicast IP address and the mask to one SAID associated to a CMTS MAC Interface, as well as associated message counters and error information.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastIndex.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastIndex
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastIndex.description: The index of this row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddressType.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddressType
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddressType.description: The type of Internet address for docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddress and docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddress.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddress
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddress.description: This object represents the IP multicast address to be mapped, in conjunction with docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask. The type of this address is determined by the value of the object docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddressType.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask.description: This object represents the IP multicast address mask for this row. An IP multicast address matches this row if the logical AND of the address with docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask is identical to the logical AND of docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddr with docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask. The type of this address is determined by the value of the object docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddressType. Note: For IPv6, this object need not represent a contiguous netmask; e.g., to associate a SAID to a multicast group matching 'any' multicast scope. The TC InetAddressPrefixLength is not used, as it only represents contiguous netmask.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAId.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAId
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAId.description: This object represents the multicast SAID to be used in this IP multicast address mapping entry.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAType.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAType
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAType.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 2.1.3.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAType.description: The value of this object is the type of security association. 'dynamic' does not apply to CMs running in BPI mode. Unicast BPI TEKs must utilize the 'primary' encoding, and multicast BPI TEKs must utilize the 'static' encoding. By default, SNMP created entries set this object to 'static' if not set at row creation.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataEncryptAlg.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataEncryptAlg
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataEncryptAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataEncryptAlg.description: The value of this object is the data encryption algorithm for this IP.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataAuthentAlg.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataAuthentAlg
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataAuthentAlg.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.2.20.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastDataAuthentAlg.description: The value of this object is the data authentication algorithm for this IP.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRequests.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRequests
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRequests.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.10.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRequests.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has received an SA Map Request message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapReplies.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapReplies
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapReplies.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.11.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapReplies.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an SA Map Reply message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejects.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejects
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejects.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 4.2.1.12.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejects.description: The value of this object is the number of times the CMTS has transmitted an SA Map Reject message for this IP. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorC.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorCode
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorC.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.12 and 4.2.2.15.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorC.description: The value of this object is the enumerated description of the Error-Code in the most recent SA Map Reject message sent in response to an SA Map Request for this IP. It has the value unknown(2) if the last Error-Code Value was 0 and none(1) if no SA MAP Reject message has been received since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorS.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorString
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorS.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections 4.2.1.12 and 4.2.2.6.
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAMapRejectErrorS.description: The value of this object is the text string in the most recent SA Map Reject message sent in response to an SA Map Request for this IP. It is a zero length string if no SA Map Reject message has been received since entry creation.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapControl.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapControl
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapControl.description: This object controls and reflects the IP multicast address mapping entry. There is no restriction on the ability to change values in this row while the row is active. A created row can be set to active only after the Corresponding instances of docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastAddress, docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMask, docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAId, and docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastSAType have all been set.

docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapStorageType.name: docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapStorageType
docsBpi2CmtsIpMulticastMapStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row.

docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthTable
docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthTable.description: This table describes the multicast SAID authorization for each CM on each CMTS MAC interface.

docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthEntry
docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthEntry.description: Each entry contains objects describing the key authorization of one cable modem for one multicast SAID for one CMTS MAC interface. Row entries persist after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthSAId.name: docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthSAId
docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthSAId.description: This object represents the multicast SAID for authorization.

docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthCmMacAddress.name: docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthCmMacAddress
docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthCmMacAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the CM to which the multicast SAID authorization applies.

docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthControl.name: docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthControl
docsBpi2CmtsMulticastAuthControl.description: The status of this conceptual row for the authorization of multicast SAIDs to CMs.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTable
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTable.description: A table of CM certificate trust entries provisioned to the CMTS. The trust object for a certificate in this table has an overriding effect on the validity object of a certificate in the authorization table, as long as the entire contents of the two certificates are identical.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertEntry
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertEntry.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Operations Support System Interface Specification SP-OSSIv2.0-I05-040407, Section 6.2.14
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertEntry.description: An entry in the CMTS's provisioned CM certificate table. Row entries persist after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTrust.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTrust
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTrust.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.1.
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertTrust.description: Trust state for the provisioned CM certificate entry. Note: Setting this object need only override the validity of CM certificates sent in future authorization requests; instantaneous effect need not occur.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertSource.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertSource
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertSource.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.1.
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertSource.description: This object indicates how the certificate reached the CMTS. Other(4) means that it originated from a source not identified above.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertStatus.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertStatus
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCertStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Values in this row cannot be changed while the row is 'active'.

docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert.name: docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.
docsBpi2CmtsProvisionedCmCert.description: An X509 DER-encoded Certificate Authority certificate. Note: The zero-length OCTET STRING must be returned, on reads, if the entire certificate is not retained in the CMTS.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable
docsBpi2CmtsCACertTable.description: The table of known Certificate Authority certificates acquired by this device.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertEntry.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertEntry
docsBpi2CmtsCACertEntry.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Operations Support System Interface Specification SP-OSSIv2.0-I05-040407, Section 6.2.14
docsBpi2CmtsCACertEntry.description: A row in the Certificate Authority certificate table. Row entries with the trust status 'trusted', 'untrusted', or 'root' persist after re-initialization of the managed system.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertSubject.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertSubject
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSubject.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.4
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSubject.description: The subject name exactly as it is encoded in the X509 certificate. The organizationName portion of the certificate's subject name must be present. All other fields are optional. Any optional field present must be prepended with <CR> (carriage return, U+000D) <LF> (line feed, U+000A). Ordering of fields present must conform to the following: organizationName <CR> <LF> countryName <CR> <LF> stateOrProvinceName <CR> <LF> localityName <CR> <LF> organizationalUnitName <CR> <LF> organizationalUnitName=<Manufacturing Location> <CR> <LF> commonName

docsBpi2CmtsCACertIssuer.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertIssuer
docsBpi2CmtsCACertIssuer.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.4
docsBpi2CmtsCACertIssuer.description: The issuer name exactly as it is encoded in the X509 certificate. The commonName portion of the certificate's issuer name must be present. All other fields are optional. Any optional field present must be prepended with <CR> (carriage return, U+000D) <LF> (line feed, U+000A). Ordering of fields present must conform to the following: CommonName <CR><LF> countryName <CR><LF> stateOrProvinceName <CR><LF> localityName <CR><LF> organizationName <CR><LF> organizationalUnitName <CR><LF> organizationalUnitName=<Manufacturing Location>

docsBpi2CmtsCACertSerialNumber.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertSerialNumber
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSerialNumber.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.2
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSerialNumber.description: This CA certificate's serial number, represented as an octet string.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertTrust.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertTrust
docsBpi2CmtsCACertTrust.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.1
docsBpi2CmtsCACertTrust.description: This object controls the trust status of this certificate. Root certificates must be given root(4) trust; manufacturer certificates must not be given root(4) trust. Trust on root certificates must not change. Note: Setting this object need only affect the validity of CM certificates sent in future authorization requests; instantaneous effect need not occur.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertSource.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertSource
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSource.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.1
docsBpi2CmtsCACertSource.description: This object indicates how the certificate reached the CMTS. Other(4) means that it originated from a source not identified above.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertStatus.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertStatus
docsBpi2CmtsCACertStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. An attempt to set writable columnar values while this row is active behaves as follows: - Sets to the object docsBpi2CmtsCACertTrust are allowed. - Sets to the object docsBpi2CmtsCACert will return an error of 'inconsistentValue'. A newly created entry cannot be set to active until the value of docsBpi2CmtsCACert is being set.

docsBpi2CmtsCACert.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACert
docsBpi2CmtsCACert.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.2.
docsBpi2CmtsCACert.description: An X509 DER-encoded Certificate Authority certificate. To help identify certificates, either this object or docsBpi2CmtsCACertThumbprint must be returned by a CMTS for self-signed CA certificates. Note: The zero-length OCTET STRING must be returned, on reads, if the entire certificate is not retained in the CMTS.

docsBpi2CmtsCACertThumbprint.name: docsBpi2CmtsCACertThumbprint
docsBpi2CmtsCACertThumbprint.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section 9.4.3
docsBpi2CmtsCACertThumbprint.description: The SHA-1 hash of a CA certificate. To help identify certificates, either this object or docsBpi2CmtsCACert must be returned by a CMTS for self-signed CA certificates. Note: The zero-length OCTET STRING must be returned, on reads, if the CA certificate thumb print is not retained in the CMTS.

docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusCode.name: docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusCode
docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusCode.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Sections D.3.3.2 and D.3.5.1.
docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusCode.description: The value indicates the result of the latest config file CVC verification, SNMP CVC verification, or code file verification.

docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusString.name: docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusString
docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusString.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.7
docsBpi2CodeDownloadStatusString.description: The value of this object indicates the additional information to the status code. The value will include the error code and error description, which will be defined separately.

docsBpi2CodeMfgOrgName.name: docsBpi2CodeMfgOrgName
docsBpi2CodeMfgOrgName.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeMfgOrgName.description: The value of this object is the device manufacturer's organizationName.

docsBpi2CodeMfgCodeAccessStart.name: docsBpi2CodeMfgCodeAccessStart
docsBpi2CodeMfgCodeAccessStart.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeMfgCodeAccessStart.description: The value of this object is the device manufacturer's current codeAccessStart value. This value will always refer to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), and the value format must contain TimeZone information (fields 8-10).

docsBpi2CodeMfgCvcAccessStart.name: docsBpi2CodeMfgCvcAccessStart
docsBpi2CodeMfgCvcAccessStart.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeMfgCvcAccessStart.description: The value of this object is the device manufacturer's current cvcAccessStart value. This value will always refer to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), and the value format must contain TimeZone information (fields 8-10).

docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName.name: docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName.description: The value of this object is the co-signer's organizationName. The value is a zero length string if the co-signer is not specified.

docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCodeAccessStart.name: docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCodeAccessStart
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCodeAccessStart.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCodeAccessStart.description: The value of this object is the co-signer's current codeAccessStart value. This value will always refer to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), and the value format must contain TimeZone information (fields 8-10). If docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName is a zero length string, the value of this object is meaningless.

docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCvcAccessStart.name: docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCvcAccessStart
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCvcAccessStart.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeCoSignerCvcAccessStart.description: The value of this object is the co-signer's current cvcAccessStart value. This value will always refer to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), and the value format must contain TimeZone information (fields 8-10). If docsBpi2CodeCoSignerOrgName is a zero length string, the value of this object is meaningless.

docsBpi2CodeCvcUpdate.name: docsBpi2CodeCvcUpdate
docsBpi2CodeCvcUpdate.reference: DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Plus Interface Specification, Section D.3.3.2.2.
docsBpi2CodeCvcUpdate.description: Setting a CVC to this object triggers the device to verify the CVC and update the cvcAccessStart values. The content of this object is then discarded. If the device is not enabled to upgrade codefiles, or if the CVC verification fails, the CVC will be rejected. Reading this object always returns the zero-length OCTET STRING.

docsBpi2CmtsCompliance.description: This is the compliance statement for CMTSs that implement the DOCSIS Baseline Privacy Interface Plus.

docsBpi2CmGroup.description: This collection of objects provides CM BPI+ status and control.

docsBpi2CmtsGroup.description: This collection of objects provides CMTS BPI+ status and control.
